# Simulator startup (READ BEFORE giving the user a run command)

The simulator is a single FastAPI process at `simulator/` that fronts the
`guidepoint`, `sms_adapter`, `llm`, and `prompt_composer` packages.

## The one true startup command

Run from a **normal terminal** (NOT from inside the Cursor agent — see the
"Why the agent must not start it" section below):

```bash
cd /Users/robertjones/Documents/newmaintenance && python -m simulator --project-root 11Labs --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
```

Then open http://127.0.0.1:8000 (Basic Auth: `demo` / `demo` by default).

## Why `--project-root 11Labs` is non‑negotiable

The simulator resolves master-data fixtures and per-user data relative to
`--project-root`, which defaults to `Path.cwd()`. The fixtures live at
`11Labs/fixtures/{customers,dealers,vehicles,slots.json}`, **not** at the
workspace root.

If you start it with the wrong root:

- `_seed_if_missing` finds no `<project_root>/fixtures/` and silently
  creates an empty `<project_root>/data/users/<user_id>/` directory.
- The next `GET /api/master-data` 404s and the UI paints completely empty
  customer / vehicle / dealer / slots panels — looks like "all the data
  is gone."
- Cached browser state then spams `GET /api/cases/<old_id>` 404s.

If this happens, the fix is:

```bash
rm -rf /Users/robertjones/Documents/newmaintenance/data/users/<user_id>
```

…and restart with the correct `--project-root 11Labs`. The seed will
re-run on the next boot.

## Why the agent must not start it

Processes spawned from inside the Cursor agent's sandbox inherit
`HTTP_PROXY` / `HTTPS_PROXY` / `ALL_PROXY` environment variables pointing
at the agent's local proxy (e.g. `127.0.0.1:55422`). That proxy rejects
outbound traffic to OpenRouter and ElevenLabs with `403 Forbidden`,
which surfaces as `httpx.ProxyError: 403 Forbidden` in the LLM stack
trace — even though the API key and credits are fine.

Always tell the user to run the command in their own terminal. Never
background-launch the simulator from a tool call.

## Optional: SMS testing

The Twilio webhook points at an ngrok tunnel. Start ngrok separately
against `:8000` and confirm the webhook URL still matches before
expecting inbound SMS to land.
